bug.short_desc: Event Dialog: Resizing the Event Dialog does not rearrange the attendees

assigned_to.name: Nobody; OK to take it and work on it

long_desc.thetext:
User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:2.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/4.0 Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; rv:2.0pre) Gecko/20110405 Thunderbird/3.3a4pre
I found this strange behaviour when i was dealing with multiple attendees for an event. Initially the event dialog showed the attendees names scrambled and overlayed on top of each other, on resizing, it gradually spaced it out but on resize back it does not arrange them back.
Similar to the Grow Only resize mode in C#.
I have attached a screenshot of the same.
Reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1.Open Thunderbird and move to the calendar tab 2.Create a new event with multiple attendees 3.Open up the event dialog, from the account as an attendee. 4.Attempt to resize the dialog box and see what happens Actual Results: Resizing back does not work
Expected Results: Resizing back should have rearranged the attendees names.
Created attachment 524204 Screenshot of thunderbird with the resize problem
First part is probably Bug 632355, don't know if the patch from that bug will help here too.
That patch won't be of help because I think it won't handle the resizing case, but i guess one can go ahead and extend the patch to include resizing as well.
